author: @b4ux1t3-tech
text: What I find most impressive about this project is that it works so well (hahaha) while only using one input (the player camera). Real-life self-driving cars use a whole suite of sensors to figure out how to stay on the road. Now, obviously this isn't a good comparison; this is a video game, in the end, he's not going to hurt anyone. But it's really cool how you thought to approach limited tooling (just one sensor) in order to build something that works (somewhat).  Great series!
